U.K. Stocks Erase Losses as Antofagasta, Mining Companies Rally

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-08-09T11:30:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/u-k-s-ftse-100-index-erases-losses-antofagasta-rises-as-rbs-shares-fall.html
U.K. stocks erased losses, led by a
rebound in mining companies.  The FTSE 100 Index rose 0.1 percent to 5,076.14 at 12:30
p.m. in  London  after earlier sinking as much as 5.5 percent. The
gauge briefly fell 20 percent from its high in February.  Antofagasta Plc (ANTO)  rallied 4.8 percent to 1,190 pence and Rio
Tinto Group climbed 3 percent to 3,489.5 pence. Banks limited
gains on the FTSE 100.  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS)  dropped
6 percent to 25.55 pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  